# Phase Omega — Premium Educational Experience

## Engine freeze

- Do **not** create new intelligence engines unless a demonstrated learner-facing gap cannot be solved by integrating existing ones.
- Metadata, internal scores, and engine execution have **zero** educational value unless they change what the learner reads, sees, hears, or practices.

## Golden principle

For every engine contribution ask: **How does this improve what the learner reads?**  
If there is no visible improvement, the integration is incomplete — fix the integration, do not add engines.

## Authoring law

1. LCE is the Educational Composer (conductor), not a template assembler.
2. Build a **Lesson Intelligence Board** before writing any paragraph.
3. Every adaptation must be a **different educational experience** (sequence, load, examples, visuals, assessment) — never clone + wrap.
4. No authoring/scaffold language in student HTML (`Notice how`, `core idea`, `Checkpoint`, `Students will`, `Memory tip`, `Picture`, etc.).
5. Cream textbook UI (`#FFF9EE`), publisher-quality visuals that teach, vocabulary cards that teach.
6. Optimise only the educational experience of the learner.

## Allowed work

Integration · educational authoring · premium UX · adaptation quality · rendering quality · publisher-grade production · golden library · editorial acceptance.

## Phase Omega 2.0 — PMES

- **Publisher Master Editorial System** is the highest authority before render.
- PMES **comments and rewrites** — it does not merely score.
- Global style guide (`publisher_style_guide.py`) governs writing, colour, typography, diagrams, vocabulary.
- Vocabulary cards are premium flashcards; diagrams must teach (caption + practice).
- See `docs/PHASE_OMEGA_2_PMES.md`.

## UEVB — final production gate

- **Universal Educational Validation & Benchmarking** validates learner experience before production.
- Not a new intelligence engine — corpus, differentiation, engine contribution, visual audit, release gate.
- See `docs/UEVB.md`. Smoke: `UNIVERSAL_EDUCATIONAL_VALIDATION_BENCHMARKING_SMOKE_OK`.

## PEEC — product excellence

- **Product Excellence & Experience Completion** audits and remediates the learner experience (writing, UX, adaptations, visuals, accessibility).
- Not a new intelligence engine. See `docs/PEEC.md`.
- Smoke: `PRODUCT_EXCELLENCE_EXPERIENCE_COMPLETION_SMOKE_OK`.

## POBR — beta readiness

- **Product Optimisation & Beta Readiness** prepares commercial beta (workflows, exports, PDF/save, UX/performance/a11y audits).
- Not a new intelligence engine. See `docs/POBR.md`.
- Smoke: `PRODUCT_OPTIMISATION_BETA_READINESS_SMOKE_OK`.

## RCPR — Release Candidate (architecture freeze)

- Architecture is **frozen** (UCF, CEF, CMIF, ULI/ULIQE, SIF/SICS, subject packs, UVIE, LCE, PQLE, PMES, EATS, UEVB, PEEC, POBR).
- Allowed only: bug fixes · performance · integration · rendering · educational quality.
- **No new engines, intelligence frameworks, or validation systems.**
- RC campaign: `python -m release --target 100` · smoke: `RELEASE_CANDIDATE_PRODUCTION_READINESS_SMOKE_OK`
- Tag when Critical/High clear: **ALORA-AI-RC1**. See `docs/RCPR.md`.

## EPP — Phase Omega Ultimate (Educational Product Perfection)

- **Educational Product Perfection** is the final learner-visible polish — not an engine, framework, or gate.
- Golden rule: metadata that never reaches the learner is a defect; surface board intelligence into explanations, examples, activities, visuals, assessments.
- Allowed work only: educational quality · writing · engagement · adaptations · visuals · accessibility · rendering · UX · performance · reliability.
- Pipeline: `… → PMES → PEEC → EPP → UEVB`
- Smoke: `ALORA_EDUCATIONAL_PRODUCT_PERFECTION_SMOKE_OK` · See `docs/EPP.md`.

## Phase Final — Content Fidelity & Publishing Recovery

- Permanent publishing standard: **if the learner cannot see it, it does not exist.**
- Repair only — no new engines, scorers, validators, or orchestration layers.
- Prompt leaks, dictionary vocab, clone adaptations, generic summaries, unused diagrams, and silent browser-TTS downgrades fail publication.
- Smoke: `CONTENT_FIDELITY_PUBLISHING_RECOVERY_SMOKE_OK` · See `docs/CONTENT_FIDELITY.md`.

## Phase RC1 — Product Refinement

- Feature-complete; **refinement only** (lesson / adaptation / visual / speed / rendering / narration / a11y / reliability / usability).
- Expand and honour the **golden lesson library** as permanent benchmarks.
- RC loop: `python -m release --target 100` → inspect → fix → repeat.
- Smoke: `PRODUCT_REFINEMENT_RC1_SMOKE_OK` · See `docs/RC1_PRODUCT_REFINEMENT.md`.

See `docs/PHASE_OMEGA_PREMIUM_EDUCATIONAL_EXPERIENCE.md`.
